Package io.github.ai4ci.config.execution

Interface DemographicAdjustment.Execution<DIST,NUMERIC>

Type Parameters:
DIST - the type used to represent distribution-like adjustments (for example a function or empirical distribution)
NUMERIC - the type used to represent numeric adjustments (for example a simple scalar or a function that produces a numeric value)
All Known Subinterfaces:
DemographicAdjustment._PartialDemographicAdjustment, ExecutionConfiguration
Enclosing interface:
DemographicAdjustment
public static interface DemographicAdjustment.Execution<DIST,NUMERIC>
Age dependent values in the general execution configuration.

Implementations supply either distribution-like objects or numeric transforms that are interpreted by execution code to produce age-specific parameters such as case rates and contact odds.
